rbina, and related families. Includes 2 unnumbered leaves of addendum (2017). This copyrighted work is presented here through the generosity of the compiler, Brian Paul Kaess. His specific permission is necessary for re-publishing, reprinting, or in any other way disseminating this work. Includes bibliographical references (leaf 44). Print version record. Electronic reproduction. [Fort Wayne, Indiana] : ACPL Genealogy Center, \u00a92010-2018."], "digitized": true, "extract_timestamp": "2023-06-02T21:55:55.056Z", "group": ["catalog-split-13", "catalog", "main-catalog-split-13", "main-catalog"], "hassegments": false, "id": "http://lccn.loc.gov/2019401408", "image_url": [], "index": 6, "language": ["english"], "location": ["neckar river valley", "cook county", "w\u00fcrttemberg", "baden", "germany", "chicago", "illinois"], "number": ["online resource", "2020-01-10t11:35:46", "2019401408", "n1043668059"], "original_format": ["book"], "partof": ["catalog"], "score": 31.833607, "shelf_id": "http://lccn.loc.gov/2019401408", "site": ["catalog"], "subject": ["cook county (ill.)", "family", "illinois", "genealogy", "neckar river valley", "kaess family", "baden-w\u00fcrttemberg", "chicago (ill.)", "cook county", "kaess, brian paul", "neckar river valley (germany)", "families", "electronic books", "baden-w\u00fcrttemberg (germany)", "chicago", "germany"], "timestamp": "2023-07-10T16:18:19.220Z", "title": "Kaess family from the Neckar Valley", "type": ["text"], "url": "//lccn.loc.gov/2019401408"}, {"access_restricted": false, "aka": ["http://lccn.loc.gov/2004695177", "http://www.loc.gov/item/2004695177/", "https://hdl.loc.gov/loc.afc/collafc.afc1981004"], "campaigns": [], "contributor": ["klymasz, shirley", "fleischhauer, carl", "brzovich, mato", "gonz\u00e1lez, jos\u00e9 gamaliel", "kubose, minnie somi", "swenson, greta e.", "moloney, mick", "bartis, peter", "robinson, beverly j.", "trbuhovic-grasa, gordana", "mack, james", "dovydenas, jonas", "american folklife center", "libonati, roland v. (roland victor)", "chicago ethnic arts project", "illinois arts council", "choi, chungmoo", "mathias, elizabeth", "bradunas, elena", "epstein, shifra", "george, philip b.", "lund, jens", "fiske-rusciano, roberta", "march, richard", "klymasz, robert bogdan", "archive of folk culture (library of congress)", "metcalfe, ralph h.", "hellenberg, antony", "kal\u010dik, susan j."], "date": "1976", "dates": ["1976"], "description": ["The collection consists of sound recordings, photographs, manuscript materials, videorecordings, publications, ephemera, administrative files, and field notes produced and collected during the 1977 Chicago Ethnic Arts Project field survey from 1976-1981; but primarily during fieldwork conducted by fourteen folklorists directed by the American Folklife Center in 1977. The final project report presented to the Illinois Arts Council summarized the current conditions and folk arts needs in a number of Chicago's ethnic communities. Materials from post-project activities such as workshops in the ethnic communities and a traveling photographic exhibit by Jonas Dovydenas are also included."], "digitized": true, "extract_timestamp": "2024-09-18T06:31:35.657Z", "group": ["catalog-split-09", "catalog", "main-catalog-split-09"], "hassegments": false, "id": "http://lccn.loc.gov/2004695177", "image_url": [], "index": 7, "language": ["english"], "location": ["chicago", "illinois"], "number": ["2024-09-16t08:09:38", "2004695177"], "original_format": ["manuscript/mixed material", "collection"], "partof": ["american folklife center", "catalog"], "score": 30.110203, "shelf_id": "http://lccn.loc.gov/2004695177", "site": ["catalog"], "subject": ["korean americans", "danish americans", "brzovich, mato", "festivals", "musicians", "kubose, minnie somi", "indians of north america", "social aspects", "oral histories", "murals", "emigration and immigration", "pentecostals", "macedonian americans", "songs", "ura senke school", "illinois", "orthodox eastern c